IMAGE TO JSON EXTRACTOR

Overview:
This project converts images (invoices, receipts, ID cards, forms) into structured JSON data.
It does not just extract text — it understands and organizes information into meaningful fields.

Problem:
Manual data entry from images is slow, error-prone, and not scalable.
Basic OCR tools only extract raw text, not structured data.

Solution:
A pipeline that combines OCR and intelligent parsing to convert image data into usable JSON format.

Pipeline:

1. Input Image
2. OCR Processing (Text Extraction)
3. Text Parsing (Field Detection)
4. JSON Structuring
5. Validation & Error Handling

Tech Stack:

* Python
* OCR Engine (Tesseract / Google Vision API)
* NLP / Parsing (Regex / LLM-based)
* FastAPI (for API deployment)

Features:

* Supports multiple document types (invoice, receipt, ID)
* Converts unstructured text into structured JSON
* Handles noisy or imperfect OCR output
* Extendable for real-time applications

Example Output:
{
"name": "Aryan Jani",
"date": "2026-03-12",
"amount": 5000
}

Limitations:

* Accuracy depends on image quality
* Complex layouts may require advanced parsing
* Handwritten text may reduce performance

Future Improvements:

* LLM-based field extraction for higher accuracy
* Confidence scoring for each field
* Real-time processing with streaming input
* Frontend interface for user interaction

Conclusion:
This project demonstrates how to move beyond basic OCR and build a system that understands and structures visual data for real-world applications.
